{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DUsxjPgQaHnksRWjXnYUAz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MZNAmW9ffS4H4DFDrFTJEp","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/tmp/agent-factoring-3/library/ccd_factor.c","old_string":"/* Match partials sharing the same large prime cofactor */\nstatic int match_partials(void) {\n    if (gNPartials < 2) return 0;\n\n    /* Sort by cofactor */\n    /* For speed, use qsort with mpz comparison */\n    int *idx = malloc(gNPartials * sizeof(int));\n    for (int i = 0; i < gNPartials; i++) idx[i] = i;\n\n    /* Simple selection sort for now (TODO: use merge sort for large N) */\n    /* Actually, let's use a hash map for O(n) matching */\n\n    /* Hash map: cofactor -> index of first occurrence */\n    /* Use a simple open-addressing hash with cofactor hashed to unsigned long */\n    int htsize = gNPartials * 3; /* load factor ~0.33 */\n    if (htsize < 16) htsize = 16;\n    int *ht_idx = malloc(htsize * sizeof(int));\n    memset(ht_idx, -1, htsize * sizeof(int));\n\n    int matches = 0;\n\n    for (int i = 0; i < gNPartials && gNFulls < gTarget; i++) {\n        unsigned long h = mpz_fdiv_ui(gPartials[i].cofactor, (unsigned long)htsize);\n\n        /* Linear probing */\n        for (int probe = 0; probe < htsize; probe++) {\n            int slot = (h + probe) % htsize;\n            if (ht_idx[slot] == -1) {\n                /* Empty slot — insert */\n                ht_idx[slot] = i;\n                break;\n            }\n            /* Check if this slot has the same cofactor */\n            int other = ht_idx[slot];\n            if (mpz_cmp(gPartials[i].cofactor, gPartials[other].cofactor) == 0) {\n                /* Match! Combine into full relation */\n                if (gNFulls < MAX_RELS) {\n                    rel_t *full = &gFulls[gNFulls];\n                    rel_init(full);\n                    mpz_mul(full->x, gPartials[i].x, gPartials[other].x);\n                    mpz_mod(full->x, full->x, gN);\n                    /* Store the shared cofactor — needed for square root step */\n                    mpz_set(full->cofactor, gPartials[i].cofactor);\n\n                    /* XOR exponent bits (mod 2) — cofactor appears twice so cancels */\n                    for (int b = 0; b < gExpBytes; b++)\n                        full->exp[b] = gPartials[i].exp[b] ^ gPartials[other].exp[b];\n                    /* Full exponents: add them */\n                    for (int k = 0; k <= gFBsize; k++)\n                        full->full_exp[k] = gPartials[i].full_exp[k] + gPartials[other].full_exp[k];\n                    /* The cofactor^2 contributes to the square — we need to track it.\n                     * Since cofactor appears with exponent 1 in each partial,\n                     * the combined has cofactor^2 — a perfect square. We can absorb it\n                     * into x by multiplying: combined_val = smooth_part * cofactor^2 */\n                    /* Actually we need to be more careful. The relation is:\n                     * x1^2 = smooth1 * cofactor (mod N)\n                     * x2^2 = smooth2 * cofactor (mod N)\n                     * (x1*x2)^2 = smooth1 * smooth2 * cofactor^2 (mod N)\n                     * The right side has even cofactor exponent, so it's smooth^2-ready */\n                    gNFulls++;\n                    matches++;\n                }\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    free(idx);\n    free(ht_idx);\n    return matches;\n}","new_string":"/* Match partials sharing the same large prime cofactor */\nstatic int gMatchStart = 0; /* Track where we left off to avoid re-matching */\nstatic int *gPartialUsed = NULL; /* Mark used partials */\n\nstatic int match_partials(void) {\n    if (gNPartials < 2) return 0;\n\n    if (!gPartialUsed) {\n        gPartialUsed = calloc(MAX_PARTIALS, sizeof(int));\n    }\n\n    /* Hash map: cofactor -> index of first unused occurrence */\n    int htsize = gNPartials * 3;\n    if (htsize < 16) htsize = 16;\n    int *ht_idx = malloc(htsize * sizeof(int));\n    memset(ht_idx, -1, htsize * sizeof(int));\n\n    int matches = 0;\n\n    /* First pass: insert all unmatched partials into hash table */\n    for (int i = 0; i < gNPartials && gNFulls < gTarget; i++) {\n        if (gPartialUsed[i]) continue;\n\n        unsigned long h = mpz_fdiv_ui(gPartials[i].cofactor, (unsigned long)htsize);\n\n        for (int probe = 0; probe < htsize; probe++) {\n            int slot = (h + probe) % htsize;\n            if (ht_idx[slot] == -1) {\n                ht_idx[slot] = i;\n                break;\n            }\n            int other = ht_idx[slot];\n            if (gPartialUsed[other]) {\n                /* This slot's entry was used — replace it */\n                ht_idx[slot] = i;\n                break;\n            }\n            if (mpz_cmp(gPartials[i].cofactor, gPartials[other].cofactor) == 0) {\n                /* Match! Mark both as used */\n                gPartialUsed[i] = 1;\n                gPartialUsed[other] = 1;\n\n                if (gNFulls < MAX_RELS) {\n                    rel_t *full = &gFulls[gNFulls];\n                    rel_init(full);\n                    mpz_mul(full->x, gPartials[i].x, gPartials[other].x);\n                    mpz_mod(full->x, full->x, gN);\n                    mpz_set(full->cofactor, gPartials[i].cofactor);\n\n                    for (int b = 0; b < gExpBytes; b++)\n                        full->exp[b] = gPartials[i].exp[b] ^ gPartials[other].exp[b];\n                    for (int k = 0; k <= gFBsize; k++)\n                        full->full_exp[k] = gPartials[i].full_exp[k] + gPartials[other].full_exp[k];\n\n                    gNFulls++;\n                    matches++;\n                }\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    free(ht_idx);\n    return matches;\n}"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequenc