{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PFY4PJ35S9krVPCPHQuKgi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Library Index\n     2→\n     3→## Implementations\n     4→\n     5→- **lgsh.c** — MPQS factoring with Knuth multiplier fallback. Self-initializing multi-polynomial quadratic sieve with LP matching. The main working factorer. Compile: `gcc -O3 -o lgsh lgsh.c -lgmp -lm`\n     6→- **siqs.c** — SIQS with batch GCD cofactor matching (experimental). Novel approach using Bernstein product-tree batch GCD to find shared factors among cofactors. Compile: `gcc -O3 -o siqs siqs.c -lgmp -lm`\n     7→- **hsd.c** — Hierarchical Smooth Decomposition (experimental). Allows large cofactors and uses sort-based + triple LP matching. Compile: `gcc -O3 -o hsd hsd.c -lgmp -lecm -lm -I/usr/local/include -L/usr/local/lib`\n     8→- **qs_simple.c** — Minimal single-polynomial QS for debugging/verification.\n     9→\n    10→## Utilities\n    11→\n    12→- **bench.py** — Benchmark a binary across semiprimes. Usage: `python3 bench.py <binary> <approach_name> [sizes...]`. Records results to `experiments.log`.\n    13→\n    14→## Archived/Debug\n    15→\n    16→- **factor_core.h** — Common utilities header (partially used).\n    17→- **verify_mpqs.c** — MPQS relation verification tool.\n    18→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f16ee78b-ee57-47d2-a561-91e9aefa955b","uuid":"9745ad72-8afe-4808-a034-3eb47b2bb505","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:48:42.862Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/agent-factoring-3/library/index.md","content":"# Library Index\n\n## Implementations\n\n- **lgsh.c** — MPQS factoring with Knuth multiplier fallback. Self-initializing multi-polynomial quadratic sieve with LP matching. The main working factorer. Compile: `gcc -O3 -o lgsh lgsh.c -lgmp -lm`\n- **siqs.c** — SIQS with batch GCD cofactor matching (experimental). Novel approach using Bernstein product-tree batch GCD to find shared factors among cofactors. Compile: `gcc -O3 -o siqs siqs.c -lgmp -lm`\n- **hsd.c** — Hierarchical Smooth Decomposition (experimental). Allows large cofactors and uses sort-based + triple LP matching. Compile: `gcc -O3 -o hsd hsd.c -lgmp -lecm -lm -I/usr/local/include -L/usr/local/lib`\n- **qs_simple.c** — Minimal single-polynomial QS for debugging/verification.\n\n## Utilities\n\n- **bench.py** — Benchmark a binary across semiprimes. Usage: `python3 bench.py <binary> <approach_name> [sizes...]`. Records results to `experiments.log`.\n\n## Archived/Debug\n\n- **factor_core.h** — Common utilities header (partially used).\n- **verify_mpqs.c** — MPQS relation verification tool.\n","numLines":18,"startLine":1,"totalLines":18}}}
