{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WSBzc1H2Czwb8aP8ruK5xK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017QQKfdzPSsdX1SmC5DAkwC","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/tmp/agent-factoring-3/expert.md","old_string":"### CCD factoring (ccd_factor.c)\nQS-style sieve with batch cofactor matching. Critical lesson: partial relation matching must mark partners as \"used\" to prevent duplicate combined relations. Duplicates cause ALL GF(2) null vectors to be trivially degenerate (X ≡ ±Y mod N always).","new_string":"### CCD factoring (ccd_factor.c)\nQS-style sieve with batch cofactor matching. Critical lesson: partial relation matching must mark partners as \"used\" to prevent duplicate combined relations. Duplicates cause ALL GF(2) null vectors to be trivially degenerate (X ≡ ±Y mod N always).\n\n### SIQS fast (siqs_fast.c)\nSelf-initializing QS with proper SIQS polynomial generation (A = product of FB primes). Tested on 30-digit numbers: 0.13s. Key advantage over LGSH: no sieve range cap (uses small fixed sieve per polynomial, many polynomials).\n\n### Simplified NFS attempt (snfs_lite.c)\nAttempted base-m NFS for medium numbers (30-60 digits). Result: brute-force evaluation without lattice sieving is impractical. For 30-digit N with degree-3 polynomial, algebraic norms at search boundary ≈ √N (same as QS), negating the NFS advantage. The NFS advantage only manifests with lattice sieving over large (a,b) ranges, which requires significant implementation complexity. **Confirmed**: NFS is not competitive below ~100 digits without full lattice sieving infrastructure.\n\n### LGSH parameter bottleneck\nThe LGSH implementation caps M (sieve range) at 10M, which is 6000x too small for 50-digit numbers. This causes the dramatic scaling cliff at 50 digits (255s vs 6s at 45 digits). The fix is SIQS-style multi-polynomial approach which doesn't need large M."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":266,"cache_read_input_tokens":263902,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":266},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f16ee78b-ee57-47d2-a561-91e9aefa955b","uuid":"0c0bb78c-94fd-4d8b-9395-d6af0eac00c9"}
