{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XgkmSLHsKSkJrqEuRSGuof","type":"tool_result","content":"    95→- GF(2) Gaussian elimination with up to 128 dependencies\n    96→\n    97→**Measured scaling (LGSH-v5, worst-of-5, MPQS + multiplier + ECM fallback):**\n    98→| Digits | Worst (s) | Avg (s) |\n    99→|--------|-----------|---------|\n   100→| 30 | 0.17 | 0.13 |\n   101→| 34 | 0.25 | 0.23 |\n   102→| 38 | 3.6 | 1.5 |\n   103→| 42 | 10.1 | 8.1 |\n   104→| 46 | 24.7 | 15.5 |\n   105→| 50 | 42.1 | 33.0 |\n   106→| 54 | ~80+ | (running) |\n   107→\n   108→Scaling: roughly consistent with L[1/2]. Key optimizations: smaller FB (exp(0.50*Lexp)) reduces matrix solver time significantly. ECM fallback handles 50+ digit extraction failures. MPQS extraction degeneracy (all dependencies give trivial x≡±y mod N) affects ~25% of 50-digit semiprimes, requiring ECM fallback.\n   109→\n   110→### ECM baseline (ecm_baseline.c)\n   111→GMP-ECM with auto-scaled B1 (Suyama parametrization, sigma = 6 + curve_index).\n   112→\n   113→**Worst-of-5 measurements:**\n   114→\n   115→| Digits | Worst-of-5 (s) |\n   116→|--------|----------------|\n   117→| 30 | 0.07 |\n   118→| 32 | 0.05 |\n   119→| 34 | 0.10 |\n   120→| 36 | 0.12 |\n   121→| 38 | 0.47 |\n   122→| 40 | 0.41 |\n   123→| 42 | 2.21 |\n   124→| 44 | 1.69 |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f16ee78b-ee57-47d2-a561-91e9aefa955b","uuid":"a4e84b17-a34a-45c8-9164-b48eef04abc2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:29:58.804Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/agent-factoring-3/expert.md","content":"- GF(2) Gaussian elimination with up to 128 dependencies\n\n**Measured scaling (LGSH-v5, worst-of-5, MPQS + multiplier + ECM fallback):**\n| Digits | Worst (s) | Avg (s) |\n|--------|-----------|---------|\n| 30 | 0.17 | 0.13 |\n| 34 | 0.25 | 0.23 |\n| 38 | 3.6 | 1.5 |\n| 42 | 10.1 | 8.1 |\n| 46 | 24.7 | 15.5 |\n| 50 | 42.1 | 33.0 |\n| 54 | ~80+ | (running) |\n\nScaling: roughly consistent with L[1/2]. Key optimizations: smaller FB (exp(0.50*Lexp)) reduces matrix solver time significantly. ECM fallback handles 50+ digit extraction failures. MPQS extraction degeneracy (all dependencies give trivial x≡±y mod N) affects ~25% of 50-digit semiprimes, requiring ECM fallback.\n\n### ECM baseline (ecm_baseline.c)\nGMP-ECM with auto-scaled B1 (Suyama parametrization, sigma = 6 + curve_index).\n\n**Worst-of-5 measurements:**\n\n| Digits | Worst-of-5 (s) |\n|--------|----------------|\n| 30 | 0.07 |\n| 32 | 0.05 |\n| 34 | 0.10 |\n| 36 | 0.12 |\n| 38 | 0.47 |\n| 40 | 0.41 |\n| 42 | 2.21 |\n| 44 | 1.69 |","numLines":30,"startLine":95,"totalLines":173}}}
