{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XWxXF45T4mweJnyShWUoUc","type":"tool_result","content":"    67→\n    68→/* Multiply two polynomials mod f mod N.\n    69→   a, b are arrays of length deg (coeffs of alpha^0 .. alpha^(deg-1))\n    70→   f is the defining polynomial of degree deg: f[0..deg] (leading = f[deg])\n    71→   Result goes in res (length deg).\n    72→*/\n    73→static void poly_mul_mod(mpz_t *res, const mpz_t *a, const mpz_t *b,\n    74→                         const mpz_t *f, int deg, const mpz_t N) {\n    75→    /* Product has degree up to 2*(deg-1) */\n    76→    int plen = 2 * deg - 1;\n    77→    mpz_t *prod = (mpz_t *)malloc(plen * sizeof(mpz_t));\n    78→    for (int i = 0; i < plen; i++) mpz_init(prod[i]);\n    79→\n    80→    mpz_t tmp;\n    81→    mpz_init(tmp);\n    82→\n    83→    /* Convolution */\n    84→    for (int i = 0; i < deg; i++) {\n    85→        for (int j = 0; j < deg; j++) {\n    86→            mpz_mul(tmp, a[i], b[j]);\n    87→            mpz_add(prod[i+j], prod[i+j], tmp);\n    88→            mpz_mod(prod[i+j], prod[i+j], N);\n    89→        }\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    /* Reduce mod f: for each degree k from 2*deg-2 down to deg,\n    93→       replace alpha^k with -(f[0]*alpha^(k-deg) + ... + f[deg-1]*alpha^(k-1)) / f[deg]\n    94→       Since f is monic in our case (or we handle leading coeff),\n    95→       we need to handle f[deg] != 1. */\n    96→\n    97→    /* For base-m, f[deg] = c_d (leading coefficient).\n    98→       alpha^deg = -(c_{d-1}/c_d)*alpha^{d-1} - ... - (c_0/c_d)\n    99→       But c_d might not be invertible mod N (that would give us a factor!).\n   100→       Try to compute inverse; if it fails, gcd gives a factor. */\n   101→\n   102→    mpz_t lc_inv;\n   103→    mpz_init(lc_inv);\n   104→    int inv_ok = mpz_invert(lc_inv, f[deg], N);\n   105→    if (!inv_ok) {\n   106→        /* gcd(f[deg], N) is a factor -- but we handle this elsewhere */\n   107→        /* Use a fallback: set lc_inv = 0 and hope for the best */\n   108→        mpz_set_ui(lc_inv, 0);\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    for (int k = plen - 1; k >= deg; k--) {\n   112→        if (mpz_sgn(prod[k]) == 0) continue;\n   113→        /* alpha^k = alpha^(k-deg) * alpha^deg\n   114→           alpha^deg = -sum_{i=0}^{deg-1} (f[i]/f[deg]) * alpha^i\n   115→           So: subtract prod[k] * f[i] / f[deg] from prod[k-deg+i] for each i */\n   116→        mpz_mul(tmp, prod[k], lc_inv);"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vo1vaXYtn8jZ5tscaqebme","session_id":"f16ee78b-ee57-47d2-a561-91e9aefa955b","uuid":"b837668f-a246-429b-8771-75e095164b4c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:57:39.748Z"}
