{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012H6DdZ4WruDGWUFFkG1gqx","type":"tool_result","content":"   480→                sqok=1;for(int i=0;i<deg;i++)if(chk[i]!=gq[i]){sqok=0;break;}\n   481→            }\n   482→            free(chk);\n   483→\n   484→            if(sqok){ good_q=1; q_val=q; delta_init=dq; gamma_q=gq; }\n   485→            else { free(dq); free(gq); }\n   486→        }\n   487→        free(crt_ps);\n   488→\n   489→        if(!good_q){\n   490→            fprintf(stderr,\"    No good starting prime found\\n\");\n   491→            mpz_clears(X,Y,g,NULL); free(dep);free(tot);\n   492→            continue;\n   493→        }\n   494→\n   495→        fprintf(stderr,\"    Starting Hensel from q=%ld\\n\",q_val);\n   496→\n   497→        /* Hensel lifting: compute gamma and delta in Z/Q[alpha]/(f)\n   498→           where Q starts at q_val and doubles in precision each step. */\n   499→        {\n   500→            /* First: compute gamma mod Q exactly (for verification and Newton) */\n   501→            mpz_t Q; mpz_init_set_ui(Q, q_val);\n   502→\n   503→            mpz_t *delta_z = (mpz_t*)malloc(deg*sizeof(mpz_t));\n   504→            mpz_t *gamma_z = (mpz_t*)malloc(deg*sizeof(mpz_t));\n   505→            for(int i=0;i<deg;i++){\n   506→                mpz_init_set_ui(delta_z[i], delta_init[i]);\n   507→                mpz_init_set_ui(gamma_z[i], gamma_q[i]);\n   508→            }\n   509→            free(delta_init); free(gamma_q);\n   510→\n   511→            /* We need the coefficients of gamma at full precision (not just mod q).\n   512→               Compute gamma mod Q for increasingly large Q.\n   513→               Actually, we need gamma mod Q to be the SAME gamma (the true product).\n   514→               So we compute the true gamma mod Q by recomputing it each time Q changes.\n   515→\n   516→               Better: compute gamma exactly at the target precision before Hensel starts. */\n   517→\n   518→            /* Determine needed precision: the algebraic sqrt delta's coefficients\n   519→               are bounded by roughly sqrt(max|gamma_i|).\n   520→               For nd relations with |a|<=A_MAX, |b|<=B_MAX:\n   521→               |gamma_i| <= (A_MAX + B_MAX * max(|co_j| * m^j))^nd / (appropriate denominator)\n   522→               This is very rough. Let's use a generous bound. */\n   523→\n   524→            /* Each relation contributes at most log2(A_MAX * B_MAX * m_long) ≈ 40 bits.\n   525→               With nd ≈ 100 relations, gamma has ≈ 4000 bits.\n   526→               Delta has ≈ 2000 bits. Need Q > 2^2100 or so. */\n   527→            size_t needed_bits = (size_t)(nd * (log2(A_MAX) + log2(B_MAX) + mpz_sizeinbase(m,2))) / 2 + 256;\n   528→\n   529→            /* Hensel steps: each doubles precision. Start from log2(q) ≈ 14 bits. */"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vo1vaXYtn8jZ5tscaqebme","session_id":"f16ee78b-ee57-47d2-a561-91e9aefa955b","uuid":"28f8aecd-79ae-4a13-a744-447ac24489e9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:16:37.543Z"}
