{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vo1vaXYtn8jZ5tscaqebme","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete at `/tmp/agent-factoring-3/library/nfs_sieve.c` (552 lines).\n\nHere is a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**NFS Pipeline:**\n1. **Polynomial selection**: Base-m method with `m = floor(N^(1/(d+1)))`, degree d=3/4/5 based on digit count (<35/35-55/55+)\n2. **Factor bases**: Rational FB (all primes up to bound, capped at 4096), Algebraic FB (primes with roots of f(x) mod p, found by brute force)\n3. **Line sieving**: For each b from 1 to B_MAX, sieve over a from -A_MAX to A_MAX. Rational side accumulates log(p) when `a ≡ b*m (mod p)`. Algebraic side accumulates log(p) when `a ≡ b*r (mod p)` for roots r of f mod p. Candidates passing both thresholds are trial-divided on both sides.\n4. **GF(2) matrix**: Exponent vector includes sign bits for both sides. Gaussian elimination finds null vectors (dependencies).\n5. **Square root extraction**: Rational sqrt via `prod(p^(e/2)) mod N`. Algebraic sqrt via Hensel lifting in Z[beta]/(g) where g is the monic form of f, starting from a small prime where g is square-free and `q^deg ≡ 3 (mod 4)`.\n6. **Factor extraction**: `gcd(X ± Y, N)` with all sign combinations.\n7. **ECM fallback**: Escalating B1 bounds with `ECM_PARAM_SUYAMA` parametrization for robustness.\n\n**Key parameters** match the requirements:\n- Factor base size: `exp(0.5 * sqrt(ln_N * ln_ln_N))`, capped at 4096\n- Sieve range: `A_MAX = min(exp(0.3 * sqrt(ln_N * ln_ln_N)), 100000)`\n- `B_MAX = A_MAX / 10`, minimum 20\n- Sign handling: bit 0 = rational sign, bit after rat_fb = algebraic sign\n- 285-second timeout"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8b55a0269e5ccca7 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8b55a0269e5ccca7' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 206186\ntool_uses: 90\nduration_ms: 2300238</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f16ee78b-ee57-47d2-a561-91e9aefa955b","uuid":"121c0c96-4207-4e77-9f2d-d0f879a164d2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:22:56.733Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Implement a line-sieved Number Field Sieve (NFS) factoring program in C at /tmp/agent-factoring-3/library/nfs_sieve.c. \n\nRequirements:\n- Takes N as command line argument, outputs \"FACTOR: p\" on success\n- Uses base-m polynomial selection: N = c_d*m^d + ... + c_0 with m = floor(N^(1/(d+1)))\n- Degree selection: d=3 for <35 digits, d=4 for 35-55, d=5 for 55+\n- Line sieving: for each b from 1 to B_MAX, sieve over a from -A_MAX to A_MAX\n  - For rational side: a - b*m divisible by prime p when a ≡ b*m (mod p)\n  - For algebraic side: f_hom(a,b) divisible by prime p when a ≡ b*r_j (mod p) for roots r_j of f(x) mod p\n- Both sides accumulate log(p) in separate sieve arrays\n- Candidates passing BOTH thresholds are trial-divided\n- Doubly smooth relations go into GF(2) matrix\n- Gaussian elimination finds null vectors\n- Square root computation uses rational side (product of (a-bm) values, with prime factor accumulation)\n- Factor extraction via gcd(x-y, N)\n- ECM fallback if NFS fails\n- Timeout after 285 seconds\n\nKey implementation details:\n- Use GMP for big integers (-lgmp)\n- Use ECM library for fallback (-lecm)\n- Factor base size: exp(0.5 * sqrt(ln N * ln ln N)) / ln(B) primes, capped at 4096\n- Sieve range: A_MAX = MIN(exp(0.3 * sqrt(ln N * ln ln N)), 100000)\n- B_MAX = A_MAX / 10, minimum 20\n- For algebraic side roots: find all roots of f(x) mod p using brute force (p is small)\n- The algebraic factor base needs separate root tracking: for each prime p, store all roots r where f(r) ≡ 0 (mod p)\n- Include sign handling (bit 0 of exponent vector = sign of rational norm, bit after rat_fb = sign of algebraic norm)\n\nCompile with: gcc -O3 -o nfs_sieve nfs_sieve.c -lgmp -lecm -lm\n\nIMPORTANT: The x value for each relation is (a - b*m) mod N (the rational side value). The y value is computed from the prime factorization of both sides. For combined null vectors, compute gcd(X - Y, N) where X = product of (a_i - b_i*m) mod N and Y = product of primes^(half_exp) mod N. Include cofactors from both rational and algebraic sides.\n\nWrite working, compilable code. Test it mentally for correctness.","agentId":"a8b55a0269e5ccca7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete at `/tmp/agent-factoring-3/library/nfs_sieve.c` (552 lines).\n\nHere is a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**NFS Pipeline:**\n1. **Polynomial selection**: Base-m method with `m = floor(N^(1/(d+1)))`, degree d=3/4/5 based on digit count (<35/35-55/55+)\n2. **Factor bases**: Rational FB (all primes up to bound, capped at 4096), Algebraic FB (primes with roots of f(x) mod p, found by brute force)\n3. **Line sieving**: For each b from 1 to B_MAX, sieve over a from -A_MAX to A_MAX. Rational side accumulates log(p) when `a ≡ b*m (mod p)`. Algebraic side accumulates log(p) when `a ≡ b*r (mod p)` for roots r of f mod p. Candidates passing both thresholds are trial-divided on both sides.\n4. **GF(2) matrix**: Exponent vector includes sign bits for both sides. Gaussian elimination finds null vectors (dependencies).\n5. **Square root extraction**: Rational sqrt via `prod(p^(e/2)) mod N`. Algebraic sqrt via Hensel lifting in Z[beta]/(g) where g is the monic form of f, starting from a small prime where g is square-free and `q^deg ≡ 3 (mod 4)`.\n6. **Factor extraction**: `gcd(X ± Y, N)` with all sign combinations.\n7. **ECM fallback**: Escalating B1 bounds with `ECM_PARAM_SUYAMA` parametrization for robustness.\n\n**Key parameters** match the requirements:\n- Factor base size: `exp(0.5 * sqrt(ln_N * ln_ln_N))`, capped at 4096\n- Sieve range: `A_MAX = min(exp(0.3 * sqrt(ln_N * ln_ln_N)), 100000)`\n- `B_MAX = A_MAX / 10`, minimum 20\n- Sign handling: bit 0 = rational sign, bit after rat_fb = algebraic sign\n- 285-second timeout"}],"totalDurationMs":2300238,"totalTokens":206186,"totalToolUseCount":90,"usage":{"input