{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0148nC32Ek1EmEVKtKNhfmjW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The thresholds: `rthr = rne * 0.55` and `athr = ane * 0.55`, where:\n- `rne = log(A_MAX) + log2(m) * log(2)` = ln(5000) + 32.6 * 0.693 ≈ 8.5 + 22.6 = 31.1\n- `ane = deg * log(A_MAX) + log2(c_d) * log(2)` = 3 * 8.5 + ... ≈ 25.5 + ...\n\nSo `rthr ≈ 31.1 * 0.55 ≈ 17.1`. The sieve accumulates ln(p) for each hit. For a candidate to pass, it needs ln(p) contributions summing to ≥ 17.1. Since ln(2)=0.69, ln(3)=1.10, ln(5)=1.61, ..., we need about 10-15 small prime hits to reach 17.\n\nThat seems reasonable. But maybe the threshold is still too high for many candidates. Let me lower it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1289,"cache_read_input_tokens":311141,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1289},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f16ee78b-ee57-47d2-a561-91e9aefa955b","uuid":"ef6bcf1c-035f-4e23-a3ac-0653d8c371f3"}
